The paper deals with person re-identification, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the vulnerability of existing distance metrics to adversarial examples, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper proposes a methodology for defending against adversarial attacks, which involves training a metric-preserving network, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves experiments and benchmarking, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
